# Preview of Calculus

## Two Main Concepts
	- rate of change
	- accumulation of area

## Rate of change
	1. y=2x-1
	- slope is 2
	- Every time y coordinate goes up 2 units, the x coordinate goes right 0 unit.
 
	1. y=x^2
	- The rate of change for the equation is x2 
    - The rate of change for a singular point is found through (y2-y1)/(x2-x1). This the m_secant-line
    - The slope of the tangent line at point is the limit

## Another Connection 
    - If f(t) is the horizontal position of an object at time t, what is that average velocity over the period [x1,x2]
    - lim{t_1->t_2}(f(t_1)-f(t_0))/(t_1-t_0)

